name: StudentAcademicFoundation-EducationalCredentials-GET-getEducationalCredentials
description: [Student Academic Foundation] GET /educationalCredentials — Retrieves a collection of educational credentials.

schema.name: limit
schema.description: The maximum number of objects in a single response. The default is 20. The maximum is 100.

schema.name: offset
schema.description: The zero-based index of the first object in a response collection. The default is 0. Use offset with the limit parameter to control paging of a response collection. Example: If limit is 5 and offset is 9, the response returns a collection of 5 objects starting with the 10th object.

name: StudentAcademicFoundation-AcademicUnits-GET-getAcademicUnits_1
description: [Student Academic Foundation] GET /academicUnits — Retrieves a collection of academic units.

schema.name: effectiveDate
schema.description: The effective date of the Academic Unit, using the yyyy-mm-dd format. The default is the current date.

schema.name: inactive
schema.description: If true, this method retrieves Academic Units that are inactive as of the effective date. The default is false.

schema.name: institution
schema.description: If true, this method retrieves Academic Units that are designated as institutions as of the effective date. The default is false.

schema.name: limit
schema.description: The maximum number of objects in a single response. The default is 20. The maximum is 100.

schema.name: offset
schema.description: The zero-based index of the first object in a response collection. The default is 0. Use offset with the limit parameter to control paging of a response collection. Example: If limit is 5 and offset is 9, the response returns a collection of 5 objects starting with the 10th object.

schema.name: superior
schema.description: The Workday ID of the immediate superior of the Academic Units, as of the effective date. You can use a returned id from GET /academicUnits.

name: StudentAcademicFoundation-ProgramsOfStudy-GET-getProgramsOfStudy_1
description: [Student Academic Foundation] GET /programsOfStudy — Retrieves a collection of programs of study.

schema.name: academicLevel
schema.description: The Workday ID of the owning academic level of the program of study, as of the effective date. You can use a return id from GET /academicLevels

schema.name: academicUnit
schema.description: The Workday ID of the owning academic unit of the program of study, as of the effective date. You can use a return id from GET /academicUnits

schema.name: cipCode
schema.description: The Workday ID of the CIP code for the program of study, as of the effective date.

schema.name: educationalCredentials
schema.description:
The Workday IDs of the educational credentials of the program of study, as of the effective date. You can use the return id from GET /educationalCredentials. 

You can filter programs of study by multiple educational credentials. Example: educationalCredentials=A&educationalCredentials=B&educationalCredentials=C. In this example, the method returns programs of study that have credentials A, B, AND C as of the the effectiveDate or current date.

schema.name: effectiveDate
schema.description: The effective date of the Program of Study, using the yyyy-mm-dd format. The default is the current date.

schema.name: limit
schema.description: The maximum number of objects in a single response. The default is 20. The maximum is 100.

schema.name: offset
schema.description: The zero-based index of the first object in a response collection. The default is 0. Use offset with the limit parameter to control paging of a response collection. Example: If limit is 5 and offset is 9, the response returns a collection of 5 objects starting with the 10th object.

schema.name: programType
schema.description: The Workday ID of the program type of the program of study, as of the effective date.

name: StudentAcademicFoundation-AcademicPeriods-GET-getAcademicPeriods_1
description: [Student Academic Foundation] GET /academicPeriods — Retrieves a collection of academic periods.

schema.name: academicCalendar
schema.description: The Workday ID of the academic calendar for the academic period. You can use a return id from GET /academicCalendars

schema.name: academicYear
schema.description: The Workday ID of the academic year for the academic period. You can use a return id from GET /academicCalendars/{ID}/academicYears

schema.name: fromDate
schema.description: Filter academic periods by their start date using yyyy-mm-dd format. If used without toDate, returns all academic periods with start date on or after fromDate. If used with toDate, returns all academic periods whose start and/or end dates are within the inclusive date range specified by fromDate and toDate.

schema.name: limit
schema.description: The maximum number of objects in a single response. The default is 20. The maximum is 100.

schema.name: offset
schema.description: The zero-based index of the first object in a response collection. The default is 0. Use offset with the limit parameter to control paging of a response collection. Example: If limit is 5 and offset is 9, the response returns a collection of 5 objects starting with the 10th object.

schema.name: toDate
schema.description: Filter academic periods by their end date using yyyy-mm-dd format. If used without fromDate, returns all academic periods with end date on or before toDate. If used with fromDate, returns all academic periods whose start and/or end dates are within the inclusive date range specified by fromDate and toDate.
